properties.NAME: Corinth Rd
properties.JUST: Corinth Rd in Fayette County is already a Major Collector.  This section needs to conform to surrounding network.

properties.NAME: Lamar Hutcheson Pkwy
properties.JUST: This route provides north-south connection for travel to/from SR 85 (Principal Arterial) & Bethsaida Rd (Minor Arterial) and adjacent shopping/schools, etc. as well as Southern Regional Hospital and other medical offices on Upper Riverdale Rd (proposed upgrade to Minor Arterial).

properties.NAME: Godby Rd
properties.JUST: Provides east-west connection for regional trips across northern part of Clayton County between Forest Park and College Park.  This section of Godby between SR 314 and Phoenix Blvd will soon be widened to 4-lanes with a dividing median to match rest of the network.  GDOT PI 0006860, Let Date:  June - 2015.  Therefore, the suggestion is to upgrade to Major Collector now with a future upgrade to Minor Arterial once the widening project is completed.

properties.NAME: Maddox Rd
properties.JUST: This road provides north-south connection between Rex Rd (Major Collector) and Mt. Zion Blvd (Major Collector).  Mt. Zion Blvd on the south end will be submitted for an upgrade to Minor Arterial in near future after a major widening project is completed.

properties.NAME: Old Rex Morrow Rd
properties.JUST: Serves as an east-west link between Lee St/SR 54 and SR 42 and provides access to adjacent residential areas.  Carries less traffic than adjacent Rex Rd (Major Collector).

properties.NAME: Mt. Zion Blvd
properties.DESC: Current 2-lane road is under construction to covert to 3-lane section.  Current ADT (10,264).
properties.JUST: Currently, there is roughly a 50/50 split between traffic that continues on this section of road vs. traffic that takes Lake Harbin Rd (Minor Arterial) east to SR 42/Macon Hwy.

properties.NAME: Richardson Pkwy
properties.JUST: This road provides for alternative access to I-75 at Mt. Zion Blvd compared to Mt. Zion Rd/Mt. Zion Pkwy and joins Mt. Zion Rd (Minor Arterial) to service trips to/from the City Stockbridge/SR 138.

properties.NAME: Mt. Zion Blvd
properties.JUST: Traffic heading north/south between Jonesboro and Mt. Zion Blvd at I-75 (commercial shopping area) generally take this route as opposed to turning at intersection of Battle Creek Rd.

properties.NAME: Anvil Block Rd
properties.JUST: Recent nearby developments, including Walmart, Villages of Ellenwood S/D, and other distribution centers have increased volumes in this area.  Anvil Block is already identified as a Minor Arterial west of Stagecoach Rd.  Most of the traffic continues east-west on Anvil Block from/to Henry County as opposed to north/south via Stagecoach Rd.  This change will require an accompanying change for the section of Anvil Block in Henry County.

properties.NAME: Norman Dr
properties.DESC: Existing 2-Lane road currently undergoing construction to convert to 3-lane section.  Adjacent land uses include commercial shopping centers, a high school, church, and residential subdivisions and apartments.  ADT (7,438)
properties.JUST: Norman Dr. provides east-west connectivity between SR 314 and SR 139, both Minor Arterials.

properties.NAME: Evans Dr
properties.JUST: Provides North-South connection between Rex Rd (Minor Arterial) and SR 42 (Minor Arterial).

properties.NAME: King Rd
properties.JUST: Provides east-west connection between City of Riverdale/SR 85 (Pricipal Arterial) and SR 314/W. Fayetteville Rd (Minor Arterial).  This road carries slightly less traffic than E. Fayetteville Rd to the north.

properties.NAME: Walker Rd
properties.JUST: Provides North-South connection between SR 139/Riverdale Rd (Minor Arterial) and Bethsaida Rd (Minor Arterial).
Provides for subdivision and school access and connectivity to and between SR 85/Church St, Taylor Rd, and SR 138.
properties.NAME: Rountree Rd
Rock Cut Rd
properties.JUST: Provides residential and school access and connectivity between Thurman Rd (Minor Arterial) and SR 42 (Macon Hwy - Minor Arterial).

properties.NAME: King Rd
properties.JUST: Provides east-west connection between City of Riverdale/SR 85 (Pricipal Arterial) and SR 314/W. Fayetteville Rd (Minor Arterial).  This road carries slightly less traffic than E. Fayetteville Rd to the north.

properties.NAME: Carnes Rd
properties.JUST: Connecting route between Lake Jodeco Rd and Noah's Ark Rd providing access to multiple adjacent subdivisions.

properties.NAME: Camp Ave
properties.JUST: This road functions as a connecting segment between Lake Jodeco Rd (Minor Arterial) and Walt Stephens Rd (Minor Arterial) depending on the user's intended destination, i.e. downtown Jonesboro, SR 138, Stockbridge, McDonough/I-75 South.

properties.NAME: Freeman Rd
properties.JUST: Connecting route between Tara Blvd and McDonough Rd.  Some commuters from farther south elect to use this corridor in conjunction with Dixon Industrial Blvd & Thornton Blvd as a bypass for S. Main St (downtown Jonesboro) for access to Tara Blvd (south) and Lovejoy.

properties.NAME: Freeman Rd
properties.JUST: Connecting route between Tara Blvd and McDonough Rd.  Some commuters from farther south elect to use this corridor in conjunction with Dixon Industrial Blvd & Thornton Blvd as a bypass for S. Main St (downtown Jonesboro) for access to Tara Blvd (south) and Lovejoy.

properties.NAME: Tara Rd
properties.JUST: Provides north-south connection between SR 138 and Battle Creek Rd.

properties.NAME: Folsom Rd
properties.JUST: Connecting route between Tara Rd (Proposed upgrade to Major Collector) and SR 920 (McDonough Rd - Minor Arterial).

properties.NAME: Panhandle Rd
properties.JUST: ADT for this section of Panhandle Rd is only slightly lower than section that is south of McDonough Rd (7,437), which is classified as Major Collector.

properties.NAME: Brown Rd
properties.JUST: Connecting route between SR 54 (Fayetteville Rd) and Mundy's Mill Rd.

properties.NAME: Tara Rd
properties.JUST: This road provides east-west connection between SR 920 (McDonough Rd) from/to Fayette County and US 19/41 (Tara Blvd).

properties.NAME: Fitzgerald Rd
properties.JUST: Connecting route between Mundy's Mill Rd / SR 54 (Fayetteville Rd) and Tara Rd / SR 920 (McDonough Rd)

properties.NAME: Helmer Rd
properties.JUST: Provides for east-west travel between SR 85 and SR 279.  Requires section in Fayette County also be upgraded to Minor Collector.

properties.NAME: Webb Rd
properties.JUST: Provides north-south connection to SR 85 for travel from Thomas Rd south (Major Collector).

properties.NAME: Kendrick Rd and Old Rountree Rd
properties.JUST: Provides access to multiple adjacent subdivisions as well as north-south connection between Flint River Rd and SR 138 & Rountree Rd.

properties.NAME: Tara Rd
properties.JUST: Provides north-south connection between SR 138 and Battle Creek Rd.

properties.NAME: Arrowhead Blvd
properties.JUST: This road provides an alternative for travel through the intersection of Upper Riverdale Rd and Tara Blvd for access to numerous medical offices/hospital and Tara Blvd south.

properties.NAME: Flat Shoals Rd
properties.JUST: Flat Shoals Rd & Airport South Pkwy provide for the direct east-west movement connecting to SR 85.  Clayton will submit another request to convert Rock Hill Dr from Major Collector to Minor Collector.

properties.NAME: Dixon Industrial Blvd
properties.JUST: Connecting route between Noah's Ark Rd and Freeman Rd.  Some commuters from farther south elect to use this corridor in conjunction with Thornton Blvd & Freeman Rd as a bypass for S. Main St (downtown Jonesboro) for access to Tara Blvd and Lovejoy.

properties.NAME: Thornton Blvd
properties.JUST: Connecting route between Lake Jodeco Rd and Noah's Ark Rd.  Some commuters from farther south elect to use this corridor in conjunction with Dixon Industrial Blvd & Freeman Rd as a bypass for S. Main St (downtown Jonesboro) for access to Tara Blvd and Lovejoy.

properties.NAME: Garden Walk Blvd
properties.JUST: Proposed change from Local road to Urban Collector was previously approved by TCC on 1/6/12, TAQC on 1/12/12, and ARC Board on 1/25/12.

properties.NAME: Spivey Rd
properties.JUST: Connecting route between SR 138 and Walt Stephens Rd.  Provides access to adjacent subdivisions and access to Stockbridge/I-75 via SR 138.

properties.NAME: Conkle Rd
properties.JUST: This road is probably a borderline candidate for upgrade to a Major Collector; however, adjacent Mt. Zion Pkwy (proposed upgrade to Major Collector) carries slightly more traffic.

properties.NAME: Thomas Rd
properties.JUST: Provides connection for school and residential traffic to/from SR 85.

properties.NAME: Charles W. Grant Pkwy
properties.JUST: Multiple Lane roadway on Regional Thoroughfare Network serving east-west traffic to and from Atlanta Airport.  GDOT project 0001817 (June 2014 Let) will connect east-west traffic directly to/from Conley Road, resulting in increased volumes over the next few years.

properties.NAME: Southlake Pkwy
properties.JUST: Southlake Pkwy is an alternate to Jonesboro Rd/SR 54 (Minor Arterial) for north-southbound traffic and many travelers use this road due to adjacent high-density residential, governmental complexes to the south, schools, and access to I-75 to the north.

properties.NAME: Thomas Rd
properties.JUST: This road provides the north-south link for travel from Thomas Rd (existing Major Collector) to/from SR 85.  ADTs on adjacent Webb Rd south of Thomas Rd (fka Flint River Rd) indicate significantly less travel on that segment (ADT = 1,760).

properties.NAME: Mt. Zion Pkwy
properties.JUST: This road is an alternate route to Mt. Zion Rd for travel between Morrow and Stockbridge.  ADTs for Mt. Zion Rd are slightly higher (13,458), justifying it's classification as Minor Arterial over Mt. Zion Pkwy.  This change will require short segment in Henry County also be upgraded to Major Collector.

Flat Shoals Rd & Airport South Pkwy provide for the direct east-west movement connecting to SR 85.  Clayton will submit another request to convert Rock Hill Dr from Major Collector to Minor Collector.
properties.NAME: Airport South Pkwy
Walker Rd
properties.JUST: Provides North-South connection between SR 139/Riverdale Rd (Minor Arterial) and Bethsaida Rd (Minor Arterial).

properties.NAME: Lovejoy Rd
properties.JUST: Connecting route for travel between Panhandle and Tara Blvd.  Development along this corridor has boomed in the last several years.

properties.NAME: N. McDonough St.
properties.JUST: This route serves as an alternate to N. Main St and Jonesboro Rd for north-south travelers in/through Jonesboro and provides access to adjacent County governmental complexes.  This road should be converted to 5-Major Collector north of the intersection of SR 138, where ADT jumps to 13,346.

properties.NAME: Garden Walk Blvd
properties.JUST: Proposed change from Local road to Urban Collector was previously approved by TCC on 1/6/12, TAQC on 1/12/12, and ARC Board on 1/25/12.

properties.NAME: North Pkwy

Also provides access to Clayton State University.  Adjacent N. Lake Dr. (Major Collector) is proposed to be revised down to Minor Collector.

properties.NAME: Church St
properties.JUST: Provides north-south alternative for travel between SR 139/Riverdale Rd (Minor Arterial) and SR 85 (Principal Arterial).  This road could probably be classified as a Major Collector but suggested as Minor Collector due to unknown ADT.

properties.NAME: Rountree Rd
properties.JUST: Provides for subdivision and school access and connectivity to and between SR 85/Church St, Taylor Rd, and SR 138.

properties.NAME: Walker Rd

properties.NAME: Phoenix Blvd
properties.JUST: Road services regional East-West traffic in northern part of County between Fulton Co and Henry Co as well as traffic to and from Atlanta Airport.  Connecting segments are Forest Pkwy (Minor Arterial) at SR 139 (Minor Arterial) and Godby Road (proposed upgrade to Major Collector) at SR 314 (Minor Arterial).

properties.NAME: King Rd
properties.JUST: Provides east-west connection between City of Riverdale/SR 85 (Pricipal Arterial) and SR 314/W. Fayetteville Rd (Minor Arterial).  This road carries slightly less traffic than E. Fayetteville Rd to the north.

properties.NAME: N. Lee St
properties.JUST: In conjunction with North Pkwy and S. Lee St, this road provides an alternate to SR 54 (Jonesboro Rd) for north-south travel between Southlake Pkwy/Mt. Zion Rd and Forest Pkwy.  Also provides access to Clayton State University.  Adjacent N. Lake Dr. (Major Collector) is proposed to be revised down to Minor Collector.

properties.NAME: Southlake Pkwy
properties.JUST: Southlake Pkwy is an alternate to Jonesboro Rd/SR 54 (Minor Arterial) for north-southbound traffic and many travelers use this road due to adjacent high-density residential, governmental complexes to the south, schools, and access to I-75 to the north.
Proposed change from Local road to Urban Collector was previously approved by TCC on 1/6/12, TAQC on 1/12/12, and ARC Board on 1/25/12.

properties.NAME: S. Lee St
properties.JUST: In conjunction with N. Lee St and North Pkwy, this road provides an alternate to SR 54 (Jonesboro Rd) for north-south travel between Southlake Pkwy/Mt. Zion Rd and Forest Pkwy.  Also provides access to Clayton State University.  The Lee Street Bridge over I-75 was recently finished in or around 2012, changing travel patterns in this area and resulting in greater use of Lee St as a north-south route.

properties.NAME: Mt. Zion Blvd
properties.DESC: Network continuity - connects two Minor Arterials.  Also on the Regional Thoroughfares Network, so should be classified as a Minor Arterial or higher.

Provides east-west connection between Riverdale and Tara Blvd / Old Dixie / US 19/41.  Also provides direct access to Southern Regional Medical Center and nearby medical offices.
properties.NAME: Upper Riverdale Rd
N. Bridge Rd
properties.JUST: This section of road should be classified the same as the section of N. Bridge Rd from Flint River to Panhandle Rd.  There is no logical reason for the jump in classification at the Flint River heading west to Fayette Co.  The only road that exists at that location is an access road for the Clayton County Water Authority's treatment plant.  N. Bridge Rd should be a Major Collector from Panhandle Rd to the intersection of County Line Rd / Inman Rd (Fayette County).

properties.NAME: Panhandle Rd
properties.JUST: Majority of travel on Panhandle Rd takes N. Bridge Rd toward Fayette County, as evidenced by ADT on Panhandle Rd north of N. Bridge Rd (4,828) and on N. Bridge Rd just west of Panhandle Rd (4,522).  There is a large drop in volumes south of N. Bridge Rd.

properties.NAME: Battlecreek Rd

properties.JUST: Network continuity - connects two Minor Arterials.  Also on the Regional Thoroughfares Network, so should be classified as a Minor Arterial or higher.

properties.NAME: Stagecoach Rd
properties.JUST: Volumes on this road do not support classification as Minor Arterial.  It may be necessary to upgrade Anvil Block Rd to a Minor Arterial between Stagecoach and Fairview Rd (Henry Co) due to this request.  ADT for Anvil Block in this area is 7,858, which is in line with other Minor Arterials in the area.  There is a previous request to upgrade this section of Anvil Block to a Major Collector, but justification as Minor Arterial can also be supported.  Alternatively, the County could also support converting short section of Anvil Block Rd between Bouldercrest Rd and Stagecoach Rd to Major Collector from current Minor Arterial.

properties.NAME: Rock Hill Dr
properties.JUST: Flat Shoals Rd & Airport South Pkwy provide for the direct east-west movement connecting to SR 85.  Rock Hill Dr. is used less frequently, therefore suggest downgrade to minor collector to indicate more accurate movement of traffic.  Flat Shoals Rd from Riverdale Rd to Flat Shoals/Rock Hill Dr intersection should remain a major collector.
